simulator.payloads

Class AtFloorPayload

  • java.lang.Object
    • simulator.payloads.Payload
      • simulator.payloads.PhysicalPayload
        • simulator.payloads.AtFloorPayload
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.lang.Cloneable, java.lang.Comparable<Payload>, InternalPayload

    public class AtFloorPayload
extends PhysicalPayload
implements InternalPayload
    Indicates True when the Car is above, below, or at Floor[f,b] but close enough that the Car should be traveling at slow speed to be able to stop level with Floor[f,b]. (In other words, this can be thought of as a "slow down" suggestion for worst case downward velocity to stop a Floor[f,b].) False otherwise OR if that floor does not have a hallway exit (eg - AtFloor[2,front,stop] will always be false). Set to False at initialization, except the first floor exits d=Stop switches are set to True at initialization.
